cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their equivariance to translation, rotation, and scale. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new module for CNNs, which is trained end-to-end, indicating that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of canonical coordinate representations suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of a classifier, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with image perturbations, which could suggest a connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
